      <hr /><a name="skip_menu"></a><h1><span>043</span> - <span>Geographic Area Code</span> (NR)
      </h1>
      <hr />
      <div class="formatname">MARC 21 Bibliographic - full</div>
      <div class="datename">September 2011</div>
      <hr />
      <table width="100%" class="indicators">
         <tr>
            <th width="45%"> First Indicator </th>
            <th width="45%"> Second Indicator </th>
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td><em>Undefined</em><br /><span># - Undefined</span><br /><br /></td>
            <td><em>Undefined</em><br /><span># - Undefined</span><br /><br /></td>
         </tr>
      </table>
      <hr />
      <table width="100%" class="subfields">
         <tr>
            <td width="50%"></td>
            <td width="50%"></td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <th colspan="2">Subfield Codes</th>
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>
               <ul class="nomark">
                  <li>$a - Geographic area code (R)</li>
                  <li>$b - Local GAC code (R)</li>
                  <li>$c - ISO code (R)</li>
                  <li>$0 - Authority record control number or standard number (R)</li>
               </ul>
            </td>
            <td>
               <ul class="nomark">
                  <li>$2 - Source of local code (R)</li>
                  <li>$6 - Linkage (NR)</li>
                  <li>$8 - Field link and sequence number (R)</li>
               </ul>
            </td>
         </tr>
      </table>
      <hr />
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <div class="definition">
         <div>
            <p>Geographic area codes associated with an item. Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/geoareas/">MARC Code List for Geographic Areas</a></em>. The source of a local code in subfield $b is indicated in subfield
            $2. The source of codes in subfield $c is <em>ISO 3166, Codes for
                  the representation of names of countries and their subdivisions - Part 1 : Country
                  codes</em> or <em>Part 2 : Country subdivision codes</em>.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div>
            <p>More precise identification of geographic areas associated with a bibliographic record
            may be contained in field 052 (Geographic Classification Code). Subfield $b
            may be used for a local expansion of a GAC code.</p>
            <p>Choice of geographic area code is usually based on the geographic names and/or
               subdivisions in 6XX subject added entry and index term fields. GACs are recorded in
               field 043 in order of importance, which is generally the same order as the geographic
               names and/or subdivisions in the 6XX fields.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <div class="guidelines">
         <h4><span class="box">â </span> INDICATORS
         </h4>
         <div class="indicators">
            <ul>
               <li>Both indicator positions are undefined; each contains a blank (#).</li>
            </ul>
         </div>
         <h4><span class="box">â </span> SUBFIELD CODES
         </h4>
         <div class="subfields">
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$a - Geographic area code</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Seven-character MARC code for a geographic area. Each geographic area code
                  associated with an item is contained in a separate subfield $a.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>043</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>n-us---<strong>$a</strong>e-fr---<strong>$a</strong>a-ja---<em><span><br /><span>[Item represented by record related to the U.S., France, and Japan.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>043</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>nl-----<em><span><br /><span>[Item represented by record related to the Great Lakes region.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>043</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>fw-----<em><span><br /><span>[Item represented by record related to West Africa.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>043</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>a-np---<em><span><br /><span>[Item represented by record related to Nepal.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>043</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>n-us-md<em><span><br /><span>[Item represented by record related to Maryland.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>043</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>n-uso--<strong>$a</strong>n-usm--<em><span><br /><span>[Collection of steamboat records relating to steamboats operating in the
                                       Ohio and Mississippi valleys.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$b - Local GAC code</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Code is formulated by attaching a local subentity code to an already established
                  geographic area code. Each local GAC associated with an item is contained in a
                  separate subfield $b. It is recommended that standard GACs also be
                  included in subfield $a for international exchange and
               understanding.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>043</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>s-bl---<strong>$b</strong>s-bl-ba<strong>$2</strong>BlRjBN<em><span><br /><span>[Item represented by record related to the state of Bahia in Brazil.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$c - ISO code</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Code taken from the International Organization for Standardization's <em>Codes for
                           the representation of names of countries and their subdivisions - Part 1:
                           Country codes</em> or <em>Part 2 : Country subdivision codes</em> (ISO
                        3166).
                     </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>043</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$c</strong>us<em><span><br /><span>[Contains an ISO 3166-1 code for the United States with no corresponding
                                       MARC GAC code.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$0 - Authority record control number or standard number</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$2 - Source of local code</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Source from which the local code was assigned. Used only when subfield
                  $b is used to indicate a local GAC code.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                     <p>Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/sourcelist/geographic-area.html">Geographic Area Code
                              and Term Source Codes</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                              Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                              Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="conventions">
         <div>
            <p><strong>Structure - </strong>All alphabetic characters are input in lowercase. Embedded and trailing hyphens are
               carried in the MARC record. A detailed description of the structure and use of GACs is
               contained in <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/geoareas/">MARC Code List for Geographic Areas</a></em>.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>CONTENT DESIGNATOR HISTORY</h3>
      <div class="history">
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$c - ISO code [NEW, 2001]</em><div class="subfieldHistoryDsc">
                  <p>Subfield $c was defined to accommodate ISO 3166 country codes.</p>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$0 - Authority record control number or standard number [NEW, 2011]</em></div>
         </div>
      </div>
